\title{cocartesian fibration}
\taxon{definition}
\author{carloangiuli}

\import{frct-0000}


\p{A displayed category #{E} over #{B} is a \em{cocartesian fibration} when for each #{f : x \to y\in B} and #{\bar{x}\in E\Sub{x}}, there exists a displayed object #{\bar{y}\in E\Sub{y}} and a \em{cocartesian} morphism #{\bar{f} : \bar{x}\DispTo{f} \bar{y}}.}

\p{Cocartesian fibrations are also known as \em{opfibrations}.}